reason.tex:
%text We only know the radius $R$ of the sphere, but not of the cylinder.
However, we can see that \underline{\text{for some $\theta$}} as shown in the figure % \begin{align} R_C &= R\cdot\cos\theta \end{align} %text
Moreover, half the cylinder lies in one hemisphere and half in the other. And so, % \begin{align} H_C &= R\sin\theta + R\sin\theta = 2\cdot R\sin\theta \end{align}
